                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.05/350: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-19T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 19, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 7:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. My 68, November 14, 4 p.m.<note n="28" xml:id="d971fn28">Not printed.</note>
                    Am just in receipt of formal note from Minister of Foreign Affairs requesting
                    nominations for Cairo appointment. Shall be asked informally in accordance with
                    practice to indicate which candidate I consider best qualified. Does Department
                    care to instruct me to this end?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
